<p>These systems also shine in multi-location setups. For example, <a href="https://babboitalian.com/" target="_blank">Babbo's Italian Eatery</a> implemented synchronized POS order management across eight locations, which led to a <strong>15% boost in kitchen efficiency</strong> and a <strong>23% reduction in customer wait times</strong> <a href="https://www.lavu.com/7-essential-pos-features-for-restaurant-profit-growth" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup>[14]</sup></a>.</p>
<p>A restaurant technology expert from <a href="https://www.touchbistro.com/" target="_blank">TouchBistro</a> explains the value clearly:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Servers can spend more time with guests and less time at the POS when your restaurant adopts handheld ordering devices.&quot; - TouchBistro <a href="https://www.touchbistro.com/features/tableside-order-management" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup>[9]</sup></a></p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="essential-features-of-table-side-mobile-ordering" tabindex="-1">Essential Features of Table-Side Mobile Ordering</h3>
<p>To maximize the impact of table-side ordering, the following features are crucial:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Real-Time Kitchen Integration</strong>: Orders are instantly sent to kitchen display systems.</li>
<li><strong>Secure Payment Processing</strong>: Tableside payments with encrypted transactions ensure a seamless checkout.</li>
<li><strong>Menu Management</strong>: High-quality images and detailed descriptions improve the ordering experience.</li>
<li><strong>Offline Functionality</strong>: Keeps operations running smoothly during internet outages.</li>
<li><strong>Upselling Prompts</strong>: Suggestive selling features can help boost check sizes.</li>
</ul>
<p>These tools not only streamline operations but also elevate the overall guest experience. For instance, by ditching paper tickets and adopting kitchen display systems, restaurants can focus on delivering consistent, high-quality meals. As Matthew Roy, Manager of Technical Operations at <a href="https://www.casadelbarco.com/" target="_blank">Casa Del Barco</a>, points out:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;By eliminating paper tickets and using kitchen display systems, we can get the chefs on the line to focus on what matters - product quality and product consistency&quot; <a href="https://pos.toasttab.com/hardware/kitchen-display-system" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup>[12]</sup></a>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>With <strong>84% of consumers now expecting digital solutions</strong> in restaurants <a href="https://www.lightspeedhq.com/blog/the-ultimate-guide-to-restaurant-tableside-ordering-and-payments" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup>[8]</sup></a>, table-side mobile ordering has become a must-have for meeting modern dining expectations. It’s not just about keeping up with trends - it’s about delivering faster service, reducing errors, and creating a better dining experience.</p>
<h2 id="3-direct-online-order-management" tabindex="-1">3. Direct Online Order Management</h2>
<p>Direct online ordering has become a cornerstone for restaurants, with 63% of customers ordering carryout or delivery at least twice a week <a href="https://get.popmenu.com/post/why-online-ordering-pos-integrations" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup>[18]</sup></a>. Streamlining these orders through integrated systems helps manage web and mobile platforms efficiently on a single interface.</p>
